reviews.text: So, I'm from NWI, aka, the greater Chicago area. I'm a pizza snob. I've lived in OH for 20 years and Ytown has some of the best pizza around. I've found quite a few gems here in Canton and Akron. When my boss heard me talking about the Italian beef sandwich(signature Chicago sandwich), to a coworker, he said, Try Burratas, they have them. I got so excited. I make them at home but it's a process and since Giordanos closed, nowhere else sells them. So, I called my husband to meet me at Burratas for an Italian beef and pizza. We arrived and it's a weird parking lot but that's typical of the small businesses on Tusc. There are 2 tables on the patio, a small round table right in front of the counter, and a table that seats four that takes up almost all the free space they have. I would say it's more of a take-out place. We ordered a small pizza with pepperoni and mushrooms and the Italian Beef sandwich. The pizza and drink prices are a little high. It was $3 a topping. The 2-topping small pizza was $18. The sandwich was reasonably priced at $11. Then my husband got a bottled Modelo which was $5! They only have canned pop so I got a Pepsi for $1.75. She said we could sit outside and come back in about 15 minutes to grab our food. I asked my husband to grab me a glass of ice for my pop.  When my husband went back in to get the food, she informed us they don't have ice but could give me a chilled glass, and she would bring the food out because it wasn't ready yet. It took closer to 45 minutes for the food. Finally, he brought the food out.  I took one look at the "Italian Beef" and knew it wasn't authentic. It was ok but not a real Italian beef. No giardinera peppers or even banana peppers, the "Au Jus" was typical Ohio style, beef broth. The pizza was good but for $18 I'll pass. Also, as soon as the food came, gnats swarmed us. Very hard to enjoy anything while swatting at bugs the entire time. Not sure we will be back.

First time in, will definitely be back. We arrived at a little rush to pick up our pizzas, the girls behind the counter were friendly, fast and handled the crowd well.

Brought home the pizzas and were very pleased with the quality. Delicious crust, cup pepperoni, and maybe my favorite pizza sauce in the area now. My husband and kids loved it too! Giving our normal pizza spot a run for their money.

Thanks Burrata, we will be back!

I will start this off with we have followed Frank where ever he goes too cook for years now. I had seen he posted that he was opening this place a while ago but we now live about 40 min from there. tonight we just so happened to be down that way got carry out and took it home to eat like I said 40 min away. they packaged it great and no reheating needed. THIS WAS THE BEST CARRYOUT EVER!! Everything was above and beyond what I expected. I think I counted 6 layers on my lasagna! bread homemade! amazing! We got the spicy Hawaiian pizza. Bomb! salads were fresh with freshly grated cheese if your even considering it...  worth every penny! I'll be back.

Normally I order the pizza, which has always been phenomenal! This time I decided to try the blackened chicken Alfredo and the spaghetti. Unfortunately, once I got the food home, the chicken Alfredo had no sauce at all, just dry chicken, overcooked broccoli, and noodles. The spaghetti noodles were also overcooked. A bit disappointing compared to the usual great experience.

This was our first experience with Burrata Italian Kitchen and a very pleasant one, from the friendly and helpful staff to the very tasty food. We did a take-out order - lasagna with meat sauce and the Burrata Box. Both dinners were hot and delicious, the salads fresh with very good homemade dressing, and the freshly baked Italian bread also hit the spot. We will definitely be returning.
